cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual SLAM and learning visual features for dense reconstruction. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the integration of learned features into a real-time dense monocular SLAM framework, which is relevant to robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a novel convolutional neural network architecture and a deeply supervised feature learning scheme for pixel-wise regression of visual descriptors. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper uses machine learning techniques for feature learning and matching. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a sub-category of cs.CV and is also possible as the paper deals with visual feature learning and matching for dense reconstruction, which is a common topic in CVPR.
